import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other', color='green')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease', color='red')
    
    plt.title('What is the trend of casualties over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Casualties')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['wounds'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Wounds')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['wounds'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Number of Casualties Caused by Wounds')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of casualties caused by wounds?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
